incidentCountsDTO Data Type

This type represents the counts of records that were lost as part of an incident.

Namespace
(Default)
Properties
name data type type namespace min/max occurs description
geo_counts (custom) element 0/1 A map of the record counts for the different geographic regions involved with the incident. For example, the following indicates that 100 records were lost in California (ID #6) and 200 records were lost in Delaware (ID #9): { "6": 100, "9": 200 } The list of possible geos (with their IDs) is available in the constDTO (geos property).
total long element 1/1 The total number of records that were lost. This is calculated by the server and is a read only property.
unassigneds geoUnassignedDTO element 0/unbounded An list of objects that describes the "unassigned" records for the incident.

Example

<incidentCountsDTO>
  <unassigneds>
    <geo>
      <id>...</id>
      <name>...</name>
    </geo>
    <count>...</count>
  </unassigneds>
  <total>...</total>
  <geo_counts>...</geo_counts>
</incidentCountsDTO>
